Affinion Group, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 25, 2017 9:54 PM ET
Diversified Consumer Services

Company Overview of Affinion Group, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Affinion Group, Inc. designs, administers, and fulfills loyalty, customer engagement, and insurance programs and solutions. The company operates through four segments: Global Loyalty, Global Customer Engagement, Insurance Solutions, and Legacy Membership and Package. The Global Loyalty segment creates and manages various aspects of clients’ loyalty programs, including program design, program management, technology platform, data analytics, points administration, and rewards fulfillment for financial institutions and other significant businesses. This segment provides and manages reward products for loyalty programs. The Global Customer Engagement segment creates and manages programs and solu...
Affinion Group, Inc. designs, administers, and fulfills loyalty, customer engagement, and insurance programs and solutions. The company operates through four segments: Global Loyalty, Global Customer Engagement, Insurance Solutions, and Legacy Membership and Package. The Global Loyalty segment creates and manages various aspects of clients’ loyalty programs, including program design, program management, technology platform, data analytics, points administration, and rewards fulfillment for financial institutions and other significant businesses. This segment provides and manages reward products for loyalty programs. The Global Customer Engagement segment creates and manages programs and solutions comprising revenue enhancement and engagement solutions that address companies in the financial institution, telecommunications, retail, and travel sectors. The Insurance Solutions segment offers various insurance solutions consisting of accidental death and serious injury, hospital accident plan, recuperative care, and lump sum life insurance services. This segment markets its insurance products primarily through direct mail and the Internet. The Legacy Membership and Package segment services and supports membership and package programs worldwide. As of December 31, 2016, it had approximately 5,500 clients operating in various industries, including financial services, retail, travel, telecommunications, utilities, and Internet; approximately 44 million subscribers and end-customers enrolled in customer engagement and insurance programs; and approximately 42 million customers, who received loyalty points-based management and redemption services or credit or debit card enhancement services. The company is headquartered in Stamford, Connecticut. Affinion Group, Inc. is a subsidiary of Affinion Group Holdings, Inc.
Detailed Description


6 High Ridge ParkStamford, CT 06905United States3,370 Employees



Phone: 203-956-1000

www.affinion.com







